comment:
* Access to low-level system functionality. Most of these are system calls. Most users will want * to use higher-level APIs where available, but this class provides access to the underlying * primitives used to implement the higher-level APIs. * *

The corresponding constants can be found in {@link OsConstants}.

* See getsockopt(2). * *

Only for use with {@code option} values that return a {@code struct timeval} such as * {@link OsConstants#SO_RCVTIMEO} and {@link OsConstants#SO_SNDTIMEO}. Use with other * options may throw an {@code IllegalArgumentException} or return junk values.

methods.comment:
* See poll(2). * *

Note that in Lollipop this could throw an {@code ErrnoException} with {@code EINTR}. * In later releases, the implementation will automatically just restart the system call with * an appropriately reduced timeout.
